91
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:23,020
Now the case is closed,

92
00:07:23,870 --> 00:07:24,700
I've done

93
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,020
what you asked me.

94
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:27,100
You

95
00:07:27,830 --> 00:07:29,170
gave me these before.

96
00:07:29,630 --> 00:07:31,170
And I haven't touched a cent
on the card.

97
00:07:31,190 --> 00:07:32,250
Xie, what's this about?

98
00:07:32,270 --> 00:07:32,930
Let me finish.

99
00:07:32,950 --> 00:07:33,410
What are you...

100
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,050
We're all friends here.

101
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:38,140
Let's part on good terms.

102
00:07:39,070 --> 00:07:39,660
After this,

103
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:42,020
don't ever come to me again.

104
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:43,170
Please,

105
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:43,930
I beg you.

106
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,540
From now on,

107
00:07:46,270 --> 00:07:48,340
let's just pretend that
we don't know each other.

108
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:50,370
Xie.

109
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:50,980
Xie.

110
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:51,580
Xie.

111
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:54,020
This was a gift, don't give it back.

112
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:54,810
- Hey, what do you mean?
- Take it.

113
00:07:54,830 --> 00:07:56,140
Cheng Zijian, you take it.
What do you mean?

114
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,250
After all these years,

115
00:07:57,270 --> 00:07:58,250
you deserve this for your hard work.

116
00:07:58,270 --> 00:07:58,700
Keep it.

117
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:00,050
Don't talk to me about hard work.

118
00:08:00,070 --> 00:08:00,660
I've had it tough.

119
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:02,410
If not for yourself,
keep it for your mother.

120
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:03,410
Don't you dare mention my mom!

121
00:08:03,430 --> 00:08:04,140
- I'm telling you,
- Fine, fine.

122
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:04,810
leave her out of this!

123
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:05,340
Take it!

124
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:40,580
Xie,

125
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:43,700
you always run away
when things get tough.

126
00:08:45,630 --> 00:08:46,420
That's not good.

127
00:08:47,510 --> 00:08:49,250
Whatever it is,
we can figure it out together.

128
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:51,370
There's always a solution, right?

129
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:54,730
Why are you just sitting there?

130
00:08:56,390 --> 00:08:56,820
Eat.

131
00:08:59,200 --> 00:08:59,580
Here.

132
00:09:18,510 --> 00:09:19,530
We're here. Right here.

133
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,890
Check out the smart lock.

134
00:09:25,390 --> 00:09:26,820
What do you think?
The whole place is automated.

135
00:09:27,870 --> 00:09:28,700
We'll check the living room later.

136
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:29,820
Let's start with the master bedroom.

137
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:30,820
Come on.

138
00:09:54,150 --> 00:09:56,100
I love this window wall.

139
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:58,100
Look at them!

140
00:09:58,670 --> 00:09:59,460
It would be so bright!

141
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,060
This house

142
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:05,010
is huge! How fantastic!

143
00:10:05,870 --> 00:10:07,580
Besides, we didn't even
pay for this house.

144
00:10:08,390 --> 00:10:11,130
Long gave it to us
as an employee benefit.

145
00:10:11,870 --> 00:10:12,650
It was free?

146
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:13,650
In Dongping,

147
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:14,610
aside from you,

148
00:10:14,910 --> 00:10:16,650
Mr. Chen is like family to me too,

149
00:10:16,790 --> 00:10:17,940
and Zijian is like
a little brother to me.

150
00:10:21,910 --> 00:10:23,700
Just imagine having tea here

151
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:25,610
on a weekend afternoon,

152
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:26,700
bathed in sunlight.

153
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,180
How relaxing!

154
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:32,130
If you want to change anything, tell me.

155
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:34,130
I'll write it down and take care of it.

156
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,530
So, what do you say?

157
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:45,180
We should give this house back.

158
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:49,610
What?

159
00:10:52,790 --> 00:10:54,060
I said, give it back.

160
00:10:54,630 --> 00:10:55,300
Why?

161
00:10:58,790 --> 00:10:59,490
No reason.

162
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:00,730
Just give it back.

163
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:02,060
If you want me to give it back,

164
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:03,700
you should at least give me a reason.

165
00:11:04,670 --> 00:11:05,940
This is a rare bargain,

166
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:07,370
why should I give it up?

167
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:08,700
It may seem like a bargain to you,

168
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:10,730
but have you

169
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:12,250
considered that

170
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:15,580
they only gave it to us

171
00:11:17,390 --> 00:11:19,250
because of our positions and status?

172
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,250
You're overthinking it.

173
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:23,490
If I don't buy this house,

174
00:11:23,510 --> 00:11:24,820
someone else will.

175
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:30,060
Tell me,

176
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:33,130
has Chen Shenglong

177
00:11:35,750 --> 00:11:36,940
ever asked you for a favor?

178
00:11:37,630 --> 00:11:38,220
No.

179
00:11:44,510 --> 00:11:45,490
If anything,

180
00:11:46,360 --> 00:11:47,940
I'm the one who's asked him for help.

181
00:11:49,270 --> 00:11:49,890
What do you mean?

182
00:11:52,790 --> 00:11:55,100
The Wan Hai case
went on for three years,

183
00:11:55,550 --> 00:11:57,060
and I was left to clean up

184
00:11:57,360 --> 00:11:59,100
all the messes in our department.

185
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:02,010
I'm too embarrassed to hold my head up

186
00:12:02,030 --> 00:12:03,420
when I go to meetings in the city now,
you know that?

187
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:04,890
Have you ever thought about me?

188
00:12:06,030 --> 00:12:06,820
Chen Shenglong

189
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:09,010
finally agreed to invest
in the development zone.

190
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:12,060
So tell me, who exactly is helping who?

191
00:12:13,150 --> 00:12:14,490
Those... those are two separate things.

192
00:12:14,670 --> 00:12:15,610
You can't mix them up.

193
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:18,250
I'm just worried you're being exploited.

194
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:24,250
By whom?

195
00:12:25,510 --> 00:12:26,340
Chen Shenglong?

196
00:12:30,870 --> 00:12:32,060
What's wrong with him?

197
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:41,250
Liu Yun, you're now involved in a
government-business partnership.

198
00:12:41,270 --> 00:12:44,010
Taking this house could give others
leverage against you,

199
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,890
possibly leading to accusations
of duty-related crimes.

200
00:12:46,030 --> 00:12:46,650
Do you understand?

201
00:12:46,870 --> 00:12:49,180
How am I committing crimes?

202
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:50,300
I just bought a house.

203
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:51,420
How is it a crime?

204
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:53,180
It's not like
I didn't pay for it, isn't it?

205
00:12:55,120 --> 00:12:55,980
Li,

206
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,700
you didn't come to look at the house,
did you?

207
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,890
You're here to interrogate me!

208
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:03,130
This is a home, our home,

209
00:13:03,390 --> 00:13:04,700
not your courtroom!

210
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:23,770
Why didn't you

211
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:25,420
tell me this sooner?

212
00:13:27,390 --> 00:13:29,100
Would you want to tear open your scars?

213
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:32,220
I wouldn't before.

214
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:35,420
But now I have.

215
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:38,130
And honestly?

216
00:13:39,270 --> 00:13:41,010
It's like a weight's been lifted off me.

217
00:13:42,870 --> 00:13:43,980
And I've come to

218
00:13:44,670 --> 00:13:45,300
realize a lot.

219
00:13:50,270 --> 00:13:51,700
Your pain and mine are not the same.

220
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:55,340
You can move on after confronting yours.

221
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:56,890
But me?

222
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:00,010
Can my father come back from the dead?

223
00:14:08,150 --> 00:14:09,300
What are you trying to say to me?

224
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:15,890
I feel like I owe you an apology,

225
00:14:20,440 --> 00:14:21,300
and also

226
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:26,490
I want to say goodbye.

227
00:14:28,030 --> 00:14:29,820
What do you mean? What are you doing?

228
00:14:31,390 --> 00:14:31,940
Nothing.

229
00:14:34,870 --> 00:14:35,940
I just want to tell you something

230
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:38,460
I've been holding inside
for a long time.

231
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:56,820
I'm a coward—

232
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:01,060
so much so that I can't even
admit it to myself.

233
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:07,530
You know,

234
00:15:08,030 --> 00:15:09,370
I've known you for so long,

235
00:15:10,630 --> 00:15:11,890
but I've never seen you smile,

236
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:13,370
not even once.

237
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:17,010
I get it now.

238
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:19,460
But I truly believe

239
00:15:20,150 --> 00:15:21,700
your parents would want you

240
00:15:22,910 --> 00:15:24,610
to live your life

241
00:15:25,270 --> 00:15:26,100
and be happy.

242
00:15:26,550 --> 00:15:27,010
Don't you think?

243
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:31,420
Jing,

244
00:15:34,390 --> 00:15:35,700
I want you to be happy too.

245
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:43,980
Goodbye.

246
00:15:57,560 --> 00:16:02,160
[Li Renjun]

247
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:06,610
Li Renjun,

248
00:16:06,870 --> 00:16:07,610
be open-minded.

249
00:16:08,790 --> 00:16:10,360
Can we at least hear
what the others have to say?

250
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:10,920
[Thirteen Years Ago]

251
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:12,610
Even if there's only a
one percent chance,

252
00:16:12,870 --> 00:16:14,180
we can't dismiss it.

253
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,010
If we don't, will you

254
00:16:16,670 --> 00:16:17,850
face the consequences?

255
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:19,220
You're talking about consequences to me?

256
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:20,820
Do you even realize

257
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:22,060
what kind of case this case is?

258
00:16:22,390 --> 00:16:23,530
The whole city,

259
00:16:23,550 --> 00:16:25,940
province, and even the nation
are watching.

260
00:16:26,550 --> 00:16:29,250
This isn't just about
legal consequences,

261
00:16:29,270 --> 00:16:31,060
we need to consider its social

262
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:32,060
and political impacts.

263
00:16:32,390 --> 00:16:32,850
And the people!

264
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:34,060
Have you considered

265
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:35,370
what kind of justice they want to see?

266
00:16:35,670 --> 00:16:36,100
Also,

267
00:16:36,270 --> 00:16:37,940
why do you think Ms. Lan
assigned this case

268
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:38,490
to the three of us?

269
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:40,460
What expectations do you think
the higher-ups have for us?

270
00:16:40,870 --> 00:16:41,980
Cases involving firearms must be

271
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:43,370
resolved swiftly and with severity,
do you understand?

272
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:45,890
The foundation of justice today
is evidence,

273
00:16:46,030 --> 00:16:46,820
I'm telling you!

274
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:47,700
What do you mean there's no evidence?

275
00:16:47,870 --> 00:16:48,770
Who says there's no evidence?

276
00:16:51,270 --> 00:16:53,010
The whole floor
can hear you three arguing!

277
00:16:55,390 --> 00:16:56,130
What is this?

278
00:16:59,390 --> 00:17:00,180
This is the prosecutor's office,

279
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:01,220
not a street market!

280
00:17:05,270 --> 00:17:07,010
I'm here to tell you
the higher-ups' decision:

